This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) because it deals with P2P networks, which are a type of network architecture. It could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category because P2P networks are distributed systems. Additionally, the paper uses Game Theory, which is a sub-field of Computer Science, so it could belong to the Game Theory and Decision Science (cs.GT) sub-category. The paper proposes an incentive scheme to improve the performance of the P2P system, which involves optimizing the allocation of resources, so it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the security and trustworthiness of P2P systems, which could make it relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
